    • Method Detail

      • intersect

        long intersect(double x,
             double y)
        Retrieves a long value representing the feature intersecting the point given by the x and y coordinate values. If the coordinates do not intersect an object, NO_INTERSECTION is returned as a value.
        Parameters:
        x - - x position
        y - - y position

      • intersect

        long intersect(double x1,
             double y1,
             double x2,
             double y2)
        Retrieves a long value representing the feature intersecting the line given by the x and y coordinate values. If the coordinates do not intersect an object, NO_INTERSECTION is returned as a value.
        Parameters:
        x1 - - initial x position
        y1 - - initial y position
        x2 - - end x position
        y2 - - end y position

      • intersects

        boolean intersects(double x,
                 double y)
        Identifies whether the given coordinates intersect any features in the spatial layer.
        Parameters:
        x - - x position
        y - - y position
